      • formatHelp

        public static void formatHelp(java.lang.String command,
              java.lang.String arguments,
              java.lang.String description,
              java.lang.String node)
        Formats the help string for the specified sub-command and arguments.
        The CommandSender will not be able to see the message if he lacks the permissions node specified.
        Borrows the CommandSender from the CommandManager; therefore, it is not safe to use this method outside of command classes.
        Parameters:
        command - Sub-command name
        arguments - Command arguments
        description - Command description
        node - Permissions node needed to see the help message

      • formatHelp

        public static void formatHelp(java.lang.String command,
              java.lang.String arguments,
              java.lang.String description)
        Formats the help string for the specified sub-command and arguments.
        Wraps around formatHelp(String command, String arguments, String description, String node) with an empty permissions node.
        Borrows the CommandSender from the CommandManager; therefore, it is not safe to use this method outside of command classes.
        Parameters:
        command - Sub-command name
        arguments - Command arguments
        description - Command description

      • formatHeader

        public static void formatHeader(int padding,
                java.lang.String str)
        Formats the specified string and shifts it according to the padding provided.
